    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-08-13T01:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-08-13T01:00:00-05:00" n="537"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d537">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">825.00 Revolutions/182: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CWS1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-08-13T01:00:00-05:00"
                            >August 13, 1932—1 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 6:17 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>165. Groveist outbreak this afternoon centering at the University was vigorously
                    suppressed by the police. Several killed and many were wounded and taken
                    prisoners. One opinion is that it is an isolated incident; another that it was a
                    premature phase of a general Left revolt planned for this week end. All is quiet
                    in Santiago tonight.</p>
                <p>Zañartu, Minister of Hacienda, resigned tonight giving as his reason refusal of
                    the Cabinet to approve his inflation scheme.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CWS1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Culbertson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
